# Vue Components

## Structure
```vue
<script setup lang="ts">
import { ref, computed } from 'vue'
import { storeToRefs } from 'pinia'
import { useI18n } from 'vue-i18n'
import { usePetriNetStore } from '@/stores/petriNet'

const { t } = useI18n()
const store = usePetriNetStore()
const { net, selectedIds } = storeToRefs(store)

// Props & Emits
const props = defineProps<{ id: string }>()
const emit = defineEmits<{ (e: 'update', value: string): void }>()

// Reactive State
const localState = ref('')

// Computed
const derivedValue = computed(() => /* ... */)

// Methods
const handleClick = () => { /* ... */ }
</script>

<template>
  <div class="my-component">
    {{ $t('key.path') }}
  </div>
</template>

<style scoped>
.my-component {
  background: var(--color-bg);
  color: var(--color-text);
}
</style>
```

## Rules
- Use Composition API with `<script setup>`
- Use TypeScript with `lang="ts"` when needed (for `import type`)
- Define props with `defineProps()`
- Define events with `defineEmits()`
- Prefer `scoped` styles
- Name components in PascalCase

## Internationalization
- Translate all UI texts with `$t('key.path')`
- Translations in `src/i18n/locales/en.ts` and `de.ts`
- Always add new keys to both files
- Use computed properties for dynamic translations:
  ```typescript
  const items = computed(() => [
    { id: 'a', label: t('items.a') },
    { id: 'b', label: t('items.b') },
  ])
  ```

## Theming
- Use CSS variables: `var(--color-bg)`, `var(--color-text)`, `var(--color-border)`
- Primary color: `var(--color-primary)`
- No hardcoded colors!
- Dark mode is handled automatically via `data-theme` attribute

## Canvas Components (vue-konva)
- Place in `src/components/canvas/`
- Pass Konva config via computed properties:
  ```typescript
  const config = computed(() => ({
    x: props.position.x,
    y: props.position.y,
    fill: colors.value.fill,
  }))
  ```
- Use `visible` property instead of `v-if` for visibility
